Arsene Wenger says Arsenal will not sell Robin van Persie
Media playback is not supported on this deviceArsenal manager Arsene Wenger insists striker Robin Van Persie will not be leaving Arsenal, even if they sign German striker Lucas Podolski.In-form Dutch forward Van Persie has yet to agree a contract extension whileBBC Sport understands that Arsenal have agreed to sign Podolskifrom Bundesliga side Cologne.The Frenchman also says that he is not concerned by comments from Manchester City boss Roberto Mancinithat he is interested in signing Arsenal's top scorer.